data:
CI - Front - Add .nojekyll file

Not having this file in the built directory makes Github try to apply
a jekyll theme which breaks the build.

In apps.statox.fr I probably commited the file manually and I don't
remember exactly how it was setup. So creating it in static is
probably more future proof.

Note that the `jekyll: false` argument I gave to the adapter factory
in `svelte.config.js` was not a real argument so it didn't do anything
and was silently ignored.
